    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati. ",
          "en": "At Sāvatthī. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:1.2",
          "pli": "Atha kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "Then the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings with him. Seated to one side he said to the Buddha: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:2.1",
          "pli": "“Kiṃ nu kho, bho gotama, sabbamatthī”ti? ",
          "en": "“Master Gotama, does all exist?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:2.2",
          "pli": "“‘Sabbamatthī’ti kho, brāhmaṇa, ayameko anto”. ",
          "en": "“‘All exists’: this is one extreme, brahmin.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.1",
          "pli": "“Kiṃ pana, bho gotama, sabbaṃ natthī”ti? ",
          "en": "“Then does all not exist?” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.2",
          "pli": "“‘Sabbaṃ natthī’ti kho, brāhmaṇa, ayaṃ dutiyo anto. ",
          "en": "“‘All doesn’t exist’: this is the second extreme. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.3",
          "pli": "Ete te, brāhmaṇa, ubho ante anupagamma majjhena tathāgato dhammaṃ deseti: ",
          "en": "Avoiding these two extremes, the Realized One teaches by the middle way: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.4",
          "pli": "‘avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārā; ",
          "en": "‘Ignorance is a condition for choices. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.5",
          "pli": "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇaṃ … pe … ",
          "en": "Choices are a condition for consciousness. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.6",
          "pli": "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti. ",
          "en": "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.7",
          "pli": "Avijjāya tveva asesavirāganirodhā saṅkhāranirodho; ",
          "en": "When ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, choices cease. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.8",
          "pli": "saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodho … pe … ",
          "en": "When choices cease, consciousness ceases. … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:3.9",
          "pli": "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī’”ti. ",
          "en": "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.’” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:4.1",
          "pli": "Evaṃ vutte, jāṇussoṇi brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: ",
          "en": "When he said this, the brahmin Jāṇussoṇi said to the Buddha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:4.2",
          "pli": "“abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama … pe … ",
          "en": "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent! … "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:4.3",
          "pli": "pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti. ",
          "en": "From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has gone for refuge for life.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn12.47:4.4",
          "pli": "Sattamaṃ. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
